  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rainforest Conservation and Support for the Indigenous Population in the Amazon Basin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&apos;s objective was to develop a suitable methodology for REDD+ based on a forest conservation project in the buffer zones around Peru&#x2019;s Man&#xFA; National Park. In addition to preserving the rainforest and supporting indigenous peoples in the Peruvian Amazon, these efforts served as a contribution to the international REDD+ debate within the scope of the Framework Convention on Climate Change (IPCC). The project should be further developed by way of external REDD+ validation and preparation of a long-term financing plan.</narrative>
  </description>
